text.tspan: Per capita organic carbon emissions from industry
Organic carbon molecules are formed from the incomplete burning of organic materials, including fossil fuels
and biomass. They can also be suspended in the air from sources such as vehicle tyres and roads. Organic
carbon adds to particulate matter pollution, with negative impacts on human health.
Data source: Hoesly et al. (2024) - Community Emissions Data System (CEDS); Population based on various sources (2024)
